        "body": "# Remove unnecessary eslint-disable directive\r\n\r\n## Description\r\nThis PR removes an unnecessary `eslint-disable-next-line consistent-return` directive in [lib/core/mergeConfig.js](cci:7://file:///Users/archis009/Desktop/axios/lib/core/mergeConfig.js:0:0-0:0). \r\n\r\n##Context\r\nThe code in [mergeConfig.js](cci:7://file:///Users/archis009/Desktop/axios/lib/core/mergeConfig.js:0:0-0:0) was flagged with a lint suppression, but running the linter reveals that the suppression is no longer needed (or the code is compliant). Removing unnecessary suppressions keeps the code clean and ensures that actual issues aren't hidden in the future.\r\n\r\n## How Has This Been Tested?\r\n- Ran `npm run test:eslint` to verify that removing the directive does not cause any linting errors.\r\n- Ran `npm run test:node` to ensure no regressions in functionality.\r\n\r\n## Types of changes\r\n- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)\r\n- [ ] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)\r\n- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to change)\r\n- [x] Code style update (formatting, renaming) / Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)\r\n\r\n## Checklist:\r\n- [x] My code follows the code style of this project.\r\n- [x] I have read the **CONTRIBUTING** document.\r\n- [x] All new and existing tests passed.",
